Peru Stocks: Aceros Arequipa, Candente, IRL, Maple, Relapasa

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-04-11T19:01:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/peru-stocks-aceros-arequipa-candente-irl-maple-relapasa.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 2:42 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index dropped 3.1 percent to 20,601.17.
The MSCI All Peru Capped Index fell 3 percent to 2,787.23.  Industrial stocks slumped after opposition presidential
candidate Ollanta Humala won the first round of yesterday’s
elections, Luis Felipe Arizmendi, president of Lima-based
brokerage GPI Valores, said in an interview. Humala has said he
will renegotiate contracts with foreign companies if he’s
elected.  Empresa Siderurgica del Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of
Gerdau SA, Latin America’s largest steelmaker, plunged 6.6
percent to 1.42 soles. Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA
(POMALCC1 PE), a unit of Grupo Oviedo, fell 5.5 percent to 52
centimos after sugar declined in New York. Corp. Aceros Arequipa
SA (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based steelmaker, dropped 5.1 percent
to 2.78 soles.  Cementos Lima SA (CEMLIMI1)  (CEMLIMC1 PE), the country’s
biggest cement maker, fell 3.9 percent to 36.50 soles.  Copper and gold miners dropped after metals declined in New
York and  London .  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, fell 5.6 percent to 17 cents.  Minera IRL
Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. minerals explorer with a gold mine in
Peru, dropped 5.6 percent to $1.36.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration company, dropped 4.8 percent to
$1.79. Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of
Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., fell 4.7 percent to $41.  Fuel refiners fell after crude dropped in New York.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, fell 7.4 percent to 88 cents.
Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s Repsol
YPF SA, dropped 4.4 percent to 1.75 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
